{"/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_noriker_ver01/data/sn90052005/00393349657/1911012801/0240.xml":{"full_text":"Richmond Real Estate Profitable\nBy N. W. BOWE, of N. W. Bowe Sons.\nEditor of The Ekhmond Virginian,\nSir:\nHaving boon a dealer is real estate in this\ncity for a long time, I would like to give, through\nyour valued! column*, my views of the real estate\nsituation here.\nA* is well known by every observant person,\nthere has been for some years a constant influx\nof much of the best material from the rural sec\ntions into the cities throughout the entire country,\nto meet the necessities of the steadily growing\ncommercial and manufacturing Interests oi the\ncities generally\u2014this being especially true of tkie\ncity; and this circumstance has had a good effect\nupon the real estate situation at this point.\nSome five or six years ago, Lee District was\ndeveloped for the fl-rst time; and so many houses\nwere constructed In that section that there waa\nquite a general fear lest a considerable majority\nof them would stand without tenants; and, of\ncourse, this produced In the minds of some persons\ngrave apprehensions lest rental values could not\nbe maintained However, the facts were not in\naccordance with these fears, for practically every\none of the new buildings, which were erected In\nthis and other sections, numbering well up Into the\nthousands, who promptly tenanted, at rentals w hich\nyielded a good return to the owners; and, better\nstill, these bouses have materially advanced in\ntheir fee simple values. This means that Richmond\nN. \\V. BOWI-:\nhas grown in the last ten years, but especially in\nthe laat'flve, and is to-day atilt growing, at an un\nprecedent pace; a fact which justifies our abiding\nfaith in Richmond real estate as am investment.\nWhite this is true of residential property in\nthis city, even more can be said in favor of our\nbutines property, which has already grealy in\ncreased in fee simple and retal values; and. as\nrentals for this class of property are constantly\nadvancing. It means, logically, that the property\nIts*If will continue to enhance in its selling value.\nIt Is true there has been some abatement in\n\u2022peculathe demand for all classes of property, but\nmore particularly for lots for residences; yet it\ncan be confidently assumed that after a little while\nthere will be a resumption of activity in that\nclass of property; which notwithstanding its\nrather sluggish condition during the latt few\nmonths, has more than held its own.\nOne other fact, an important one, should be_1\ntorne in mind, and it is this: real estate is the\nmost solid form of investment, suffering less from\nbusiness depression and paniis than any other\nform of investment; while, unlike railroad bonds,\nor securities of that class, which seldom enhance\nto any appreciable extent, real estate, in a city i\nlike this, is ever increasing in value.\nWith many good wishes for The Virginian, 1 am.\nYours sincerely,\nN. W. BOWE.\nof N. W. riowe Sou\nReal Estate Basis of All Value\nBy H. R. POLLARD, of Pollard Bagby.\nKmI \u00abetate Is the baste of all raises. 1* it not\ngtrmago U be diMTtniMle) BgJwt by\n\u2022he DaM BMW MUBf M? I kB\u00abi never\nknown bow thin boo to bn >\u2014srt, bnt I \u00abt\npect 1U history woold bn an tatnreottoc some\nof the tariff schedules that happen to be bn tbe\nstatute book*.\nSafety for fimotment: After eighteen years\u2019\nexperience X am satisfied that there no inrest\nment bo safe o tbo sure as Richmond dty real es\ntate.\nla all these yean we hare seen investments made\nIn thousand* of cases, and ninety-nine times out\nof erary hundred, they hare been absolutely safe,\nand barn retained a reasonable dividend each year\nTbe fhet Oat an Investor should want real es\ntate to pay him from six to eight per eent net,\nwhen Government Bonds only pay two and n half\nper cant, Stats Bands throe per oent and City\nBonds four per east. In somethin* that I have\nnever been this